From df6ba0a83fabf56d47241a798170907f699f2e76 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Lars-Peter Clausen <lars@metafoo.de>
Date: Mon, 29 Oct 2012 13:49:07 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 261/509] ASoC: xilinx-pcm: Reduce preallocated memory area

https://github.com/analogdevicesinc/linux.git xcomm_zynq
commit 0f8dd21d5a75da378066468228eba03333f2b4cf

We are running a little tight on DMAable memory otherwise if we have all three
audio, video and xcomm running.

Signed-off-by: Lars-Peter Clausen <lars@metafoo.de>
Signed-off-by: Zhong Hongbo <hongbo.zhong@windriver.com>
---
 sound/soc/xlnx/xilinx-pcm.c |    2 +-
 1 files changed, 1 insertions(+), 1 deletions(-)

diff --git a/sound/soc/xlnx/xilinx-pcm.c b/sound/soc/xlnx/xilinx-pcm.c
index a9680aa..f304924 100644
--- a/sound/soc/xlnx/xilinx-pcm.c
+++ b/sound/soc/xlnx/xilinx-pcm.c
@@ -83,7 +83,7 @@ static int xlnx_pcm_new(struct snd_soc_pcm_runtime *rtd)
 
 	return snd_pcm_lib_preallocate_pages_for_all(rtd->pcm,
 		SNDRV_DMA_TYPE_DEV,
-		card->dev, 8 * 1024 * 1024,
+		card->dev, 1 * 1024 * 1024,
 		xlnx_pcm_hardware.buffer_bytes_max);
 }
 
